  <h1><i>Lesson 3: Building Installation Media</i></h1>
  <ul>
    <li>Mac OS cannot be bought directly like Windows can. It must be installed on a new or existing machine</li>
    <h3>Scenario: Mac with a Broken Hard Drive that needs OS Reinstall</h3>
    <li>The slow way would be to Download OS & Recover it from the internet</li>
    <li>The fast way would be to go to another Mac Device and reinstall the OS from a USB Installer.</li>
    <li>USB Keys can be used to troubleshoot and recover.</li>
    <li>Boot the recovery partition off the USB even if you can't access the one present on-disk</li>
  </ul>
